# Installation

Edit the webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml file in the directory of the running 
instance of basex.

Edit the following entries:

<context-param>
  <param-name>org.basex.webpath</param-name>
  <param-value>/Users/sloiseau/Recherche/Corpus/workspace/xq4interlinear/webapp</param-value>
</context-param>  

<context-param>
  <param-name>org.basex.restpath</param-name>
  <param-value>/Users/sloiseau/Recherche/Corpus/workspace/xq4interlinear</param-value>
</context-param>  

<context-param>
  <param-name>org.basex.dbpath</param-name>
  <param-value>/Users/sloiseau/Recherche/Corpus/Corpus/BasexData/data</param-value>
</context-param>  

OR the corresponding field in {running instance dir}/.basex

In order for the xslt transformation to work, you shoud add the saxon XSLT 
engine on the CLASSPATH when lauching the basexhttp script:
CP=$MAIN/BaseX.jar:$MAIN/lib/custom/*:$MAIN/lib/*:$CLASSPATH:/Applications/SaxonHE9-9-1-3J/saxon9he.jar


The static files are still in the basex/web-app directory

cp /home/sylvain/Workspace/Rest4Interlinear/webapp/static/js/* /opt/BaseX933/basex/webapp/static/
cp /home/sylvain/Workspace/Rest4Interlinear/webapp/static/css/* /opt/BaseX933/basex/webapp/static/

# Run

from the home directory containing the .basex file, with:

    bash /opt/BaseX933/basex/bin/basexhttp

